The paper deals with optimization problems with constraints, which are typically studied in the subfield of computational game theory (cs.GT) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of algorithms and competitive analysis suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the study of inequalities and generalizations of well-known problems is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG).
